main event: A round, large, white object with a brilliant white streak was observed flying in a straight course from east to west over Orlando, Florida on 4th July 1955 for sixty to seventy seconds.
interesting points: The object was observed by both military and civilian sources.
Observers in Miami and Palm Beach also sighted the same object.
The report suggested that the object was likely a meteorite based on its description and the duration of the sighting.
Speculation arose due to the brightness of the meteorite.
Photographs were taken during the sighting.
sighted object: round, large, white object with a brilliant streak
